 of information and the production of meaning within early modern European culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aTragedyxHistory and criticism. 4aShakespeare 2018. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Shakespeare.2bisacsh  aAll's Well That Ends Well.  aAntony and Cleopatra.  aGiletta of Narbonne.  aHamlet.  aHélène of Tournon.  aJacques Grévin.  aMargreta De Grazia.  aMichel de Montaigne.  aRobert Garnier.  aShakespearean Tragic.  aÉtienne Jodelle.1 aHillman, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613509440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526135094423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526135094/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles